BlockPublicAccessConfiguration.documentation: Allows the customer to block public security group rules in future cluster launches, ignoring a whitelisted range of ports provided by the customer

TopologyComponentOverlays.documentation: TopologyComponentOverlay is a list of components (with names) associated with a specific cluster topology. Existing cluster topology are solonode-classic, multinode-classic, multinode-ha. Currently only a single TopologyComponentOverlay is expected in a ComponentBundle but for future extension a list of TopologyComponentOverlay presents as a member of ComponentBundle object.

GetBlockPublicAccessConfigurationInput.documentation: Retrieves the BlockPublicAccessConfiguration for the calling account id.

OnDemandSpecification.documentation: OnDemandSpecification is an optional parameter to specify the AllocationStrategy and CapacityReservationOptions. AllocationStrategy is for the order of the instance types to use in fulfilling On-Demand capacity. Setting this, to any value, will trigger the use of the EC2 CreateFleet API. See https://quip-amazon.com/qW40AaKoPa6U/EMR-Public-API-change-for-FFP-Integration for more info If AllocationStrategy if specified as lowest-price, EMR uses price to determine the order, launching the lowest price first. If AllocationStrategy is specified as flexible, EMR will use Flexible Fleet Pricing to fulfill the on-demand capacity. EMR defaults to lowest-price for AllocationStrategy and does not use the EC2 CreateFleet API without this parameter. CapacityReservationOptions is the on-demand capacity reservation specifications for UsageStrategy and CapacityReservationPreference. See https://sim.amazon.com/issues/EMR-12812 for more info.

InstanceGroupProvisioningSpecifications.documentation: InstanceGroupProvisioningSpecifications is an optional parameter to specify the provisioning specifications for instances under certain instance roles (Master/Core/Task), determining TargetOnDemandCapacity and TargetSpotCapacity. It also used to specify allocation strategy for on-demand and sport market types. This field is introduced to store the intent of customer on how to provision each node type, in terms of the aggregate capacity. This field can be used only with InstanceGroups configuration option. This field must be used together with WeightedCapacity in InstanceGroupConfig rather than InstanceCount. The two options of WeightedCapacity and InstanceCount in InstanceGroupConfig are mutually exclusive. TargetOnDemandCapacity is the target capacity of On-Demand units for the instances under the node type, which determines how many On-Demand Instances to provision. TargetSpotCapacity is the target capacity of Spot units for the instances under the node type, which determines how many Spot Instances to provision. See https://sim.amazon.com/issues/EMR-18571 for more info.

AllocationStrategy.documentation: If specified as lowest-price, EMR uses price to determine the order, launching the lowest price first. If specified as flexible, EMR will use Flexible Fleet Pricing to fulfill the on-demand capacity.

CapacityReservationOptions.documentation: UsageStrategy indicates whether to use unused Capacity Reservations for fulfilling On-Demand capacity. If specified as use-capacity-reservations-first, EMR will use unused Capacity Reservations to fulfill On-Demand capacity up to the target On-Demand capacity. CapacityReservationPreference indicates the instance's Capacity Reservation preferences. If specified as open, EMR will launch instances in any open Capacity Reservation that has matching attributes (instance type, platform, Availability Zone). If specified as none, EMR will avoid launching instances in a Capacity Reservation even if one is available. The instance runs in On-Demand capacity. EMR defaults to open for CapacityReservationPreference. CapacityReservationResourceGroupArn indicates the ARN of the Capacity Reservation resource group in which to run the instance. This field can be used only with InstanceFleets configuration.

OnDemandResizingSpecification.documentation: The resize specification for OnDemand Instances. For InstanceFleet configuration, it specifies the timeout duration for scale-up operations.

Port.documentation: EC2 Security Group Network port ranging from -1 to 65535.

PortRange.documentation: A range of EC2 security group ports.

RepositoryBranch.documentation: This refers to the repository branch name. The pattern for validation follows the guidelines specified in git docs for git-check-ref-format. Refer: https://mirrors.edge.kernel.org/pub/software/scm/git/docs/git-check-ref-format.html. Using branch length from SageMaker documentation: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sagemaker/latest/dg/API_GitConfig.html

RepositoryUrl.documentation: This refers to the repository url. The pattern for validation accepts a valid url starting with prefix "https://"

SpotProvisioningSpecification.documentation: The launch specification for Spot Instances. For InstanceFleet configuration, it specifies the defined duration, provisioning timeout behavior and allocation strategy. For InstanceGroups configuration, only allocation strategy can be specified.

SpotResizingSpecification.documentation: The resize specification for Spot Instances. For InstanceFleet configuration, it specifies the timeout duration and timeoutAction for scale-up operations.

TopologyComponentOverlay.documentation: TopologyComponentOverlay is a list of components (with names) associated with a specific cluster topology

TopologyComponentOverlayList.documentation: A list of TopologyComponentOverlays as part of the ComponentBundle
